  "paths": {
    "/reporting/reports/{reportId}": {
      "get": {
        "description": "Gets a generation status of a report by id. Uses the `reportId` value from\nthe response of previously requested report via `POST /reporting/reports`\noperation. When `status` is set to `COMPLETED`, the report will be\navailable to be downloaded at `url`.\n\nReport generation can take as long as 3 hours. Repeated calls to check report status may generate a 429 response,\nindicating that your requests have been throttled. To retrieve reports programmatically, your application logic should\ninstitute a delay between requests. For more information,\nsee [Retry logic with exponential backoff](concepts/rate-limiting#use-retry-logic-with-exponential-backoff).\n\n\n**Authorized resource type**:\nGlobal Ad Account ID, Profile ID\n\n**Parameter name**:\nAmazon-Advertising-API-Scope\n\n**Parameter in**:\nheader\n\n**Requires one of these permissions**:\n[\"advertiser_campaign_edit\",\"advertiser_campaign_view\",\"nemo_report_edit\",\"nemo_report_view\",\"reports_edit\"]\n\n**Authorized resource type**:\nDSP Rodeo Entity ID, DSP Advertiser Account ID\n\n**Parameter name**:\nAmazon-Ads-AccountId\n\n**Parameter in**:\nheader\n\n**Requires one of these permissions**:\n[\"advertiser_campaign_edit\",\"advertiser_campaign_view\",\"nemo_report_edit\",\"nemo_report_view\",\"reports_edit\",\"view_performance_dashboard\"]",
        "operationId": "getAsyncReport",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "description": "The identifier of the requested report.",
            "in": "path",
            "name": "reportId",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "description": "The identifier of a client associated with a \"Login with Amazon\" account.",
            "in": "header",
            "name": "Amazon-Advertising-API-ClientId",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "description": "The identifier of a profile associated with the advertiser account. Use GET method on Profiles resource to list profiles associated with the access token passed in the HTTP Authorization header.",
            "in": "header",
            "name": "Amazon-Advertising-API-Scope",
            "required": false,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "description": "The identifier of a DSP advertiser account. Optional. For details, see [this guide](guides/reporting/dsp/creating-reports).",
            "in": "header",
            "name": "Amazon-Ads-AccountId",
            "required": false,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          }
        ],
